data.sampled:
28BYJ-48 is an 5V Stepper Motor with 28 teeth and 48 pulses per revolution. To find the gear ratio, first calculate the number of steps per cm:

n\_steps/cm = steps/revolution \* pulses/step
n\_steps/cm = 48 \* 28 ≈ 1280

Next, determine the number of teeth on the gear:

n\_teeth = (n\_steps/cm) / gear\_ratio
n\_teeth = 1280 / gear\_ratio ≈ 28

The gear ratio is the ratio between the number of teeth on the gear and the number of teeth on the motor. In this case, the gear ratio is approximately 28:28.
